message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Albania, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling to the grocery store can be a quick and convenient option. It will take you around 5-10 minutes to reach your destination.

3. Public transportation: Depending on the availability of public transportation in your area, you can check if there are any buses or minibusses that pass by or near the grocery store. This can be a cost-effective option, but the frequency and routes of public transportation may vary.

4. Taxi or rideshare: If you prefer a more comfortable and direct option, you can take a taxi or use a ridesharing service like Uber or Bolt. This will be the quickest way to reach the grocery store, but it will also be the most expensive.

Consider your preferences, the weather conditions, and the availability of transportation options to choose the most suitable method for your trip to the grocery store.
